{
  "texts": [
    "It provides guidance to actuaries on appropriate model governance to manage the risks inherent in using a model.",
    "Model governance is important for all models, from those using simple spreadsheets to those including complex simulations.",
    "The level of governance should be proportionate to the risk to the intended users as a result of an incorrect conclusion being drawn from the results of the model\" FCA Principles for Businesses Principle 9 on relationships of trust with customers states: \"A firm must take reasonable care to ensure the suitability of its advice and discretionary decisions for any customer who is entitled to rely upon its judgement\"",
    "14 EY offers a brief discussion about the EU AI Act and its impact on risk management and governance of insurers (Kolding, 2022).",
    "the focus is on items classed as high risk and Canada's AI and Data Act (Innovation, Science and Economic Development Canada, 2023))."
